{"word":"ἅπας","slug":"ἅπας","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἅπας, ασα, αν</el></b> [<el>ἀ-</el> (<el>ἁ-</el>) <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ copul.\">copul.</a>, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πᾶς\">πᾶς</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> with noun and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ art.\">art.</a>, of a totality <b><i>whole</i> <a href='B:490 3:21'>Lk 3:21</a>; <a href='B:490 8:37'>8:37</a>; <a href='B:510 25:24'>Ac 25:24</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> without <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ art.\">art.</a>, of every item or <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> in an aggregate <b><i>all, everybody, everything</i> <a href='B:470 24:39'>Mt 24:39</a>; <a href='B:480 16:15'>Mk 16:15</a></b> (every part of the world); <b><a href='B:490 5:26'>Lk 5:26</a>; <a href='B:510 2:44'>Ac 2:44</a>; <a href='B:550 3:28'>Gal 3:28</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> A common term, along with <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πᾶς\">πᾶς</a></el>, in Luke-Acts. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπαρχή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπασπάζομαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}